"title": "5126: arm",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5126",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Used as a symbol of strength and as a means of expressing affection and relationship. Some ornaments are worn on the arm.</p>\n<h2>Everyday uses of arms</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:12\">NUM 11:12</a> <em>carrying</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:11\">NUM 20:11</a> <em>hitting</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:35\">2SA 22:35</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:34\">PSA 18:34</a> <em>archery</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:18\">2KI 5:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs7:2\">2KI 7:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs7:17\">2KI 7:17</a>PSA <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs129:7\">129:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa17:5\">ISA 17:5</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:12\">ISA 44:12</a> <em>craftsmanship</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:3\">HOS 11:3</a> <em>teaching to walk</em></p>\n<h2>The arm as a symbol of human strength</h2>\n<h3>Of physical strength in general</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:24\">GEN 49:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg15:14\">JDG 15:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:12\">JDG 16:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:17\">PRO 31:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:12\">ISA 44:12</a></p>\n<h3>Of strength for battle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek30:24-Ezek30:25\">EZK 30:24–30:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job35:9\">JOB 35:9</a></p>\n<h2>The arm as a symbol of human weakness</h2>\n<h3>A broken arm expresses defeat</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:25\">JER 48:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:15\">JOB 38:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:15\">PSA 10:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek30:21-Ezek30:22\">EZK 30:21–30:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek30:24-Ezek30:25\">EZK 30:24–30:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech11:17\">ZEC 11:17</a></p>\n<h3>Restrained arms</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer40:4\">JER 40:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:7\">ACT 12:7</a></p>\n<h3>Feeble arms need to be strengthened</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job26:2\">JOB 26:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:12\">HEB 12:12</a></p>\n<h3>Human arms are weak compared with God's strength</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job40:9\">JOB 40:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:8\">2CH 32:8</a></p>\n<h2>The arm of God as a symbol</h2>\n<h3>Of the might of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:15\">PSA 77:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:10\">PSA 89:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:13\">PSA 89:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:12\">ISA 63:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer27:5\">JER 27:5</a></p>\n<h3>Of the power of God to save</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:23\">NUM 11:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:6\">EXO 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:29\">DEU 9:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:27\">DEU 33:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:32\">2CH 6:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:1\">ISA 53:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:1\">ISA 59:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:16\">ISA 59:16</a></p>\n<h3>Of the eternity of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:27\">DEU 33:27</a></p>\n<h3>Of the holiness of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps98:1\">PSA 98:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:10\">ISA 52:10</a></p>\n<h2>Arms as an expression of affection and greeting</h2>\n<h3>Used to embrace in greeting</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:14\">GEN 45:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:13\">GEN 29:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen33:4\">GEN 33:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:29\">GEN 46:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:10\">GEN 48:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:20\">LUK 15:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:37\">ACT 20:37</a></p>\n<h3>Used to embrace a wife or lover</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:6\">SNG 2:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:5\">GEN 16:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:8\">2SA 12:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:20\">PRO 5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song8:3\">SNG 8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:5\">MIC 7:5</a></p>\n<h3>Used to embrace the young</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:16\">MRK 10:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:12\">NUM 11:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:3\">2SA 12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:19\">1KI 17:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:23\">1KI 17:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:16\">2KI 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:22\">ISA 49:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:12\">LAM 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:36\">MRK 9:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:28\">LUK 2:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:10\">ACT 20:10</a></p>\n<h3>Open arms express generosity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:20\">PRO 31:20</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Used in phrases expressing the adoption of false gods</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:9\">1KI 9:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:22\">2CH 7:22</a></p>\n<h2>The beauty of the arm</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song5:14\">SNG 5:14</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Objects worn on the arm</h2>\n<h3>Ornaments</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:30\">GEN 24:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:47\">GEN 24:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:50\">NUM 31:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:10\">2SA 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:18-Isa3:19\">ISA 3:18–3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:11\">EZK 16:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:42\">EZK 23:42</a></p>\n<h3>Identification marks</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:28\">GEN 38:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:30\">GEN 38:30</a></p>\n<h3>Magic charms</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:18\">EZK 13:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:20\">EZK 13:20</a></p>",
